end certain types of alerts, you can disable them at the system level."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Are notifications secure and HIPAA-compliant?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Notifications sent through external channels such as email, SMS, or push never include PII or PHI. Patients receive secure links to log into the portal or mobile app to view sensitive details, supporting HIPAA compliance."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can patients respond to notifications?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Notifications can be interactive. Patients can confirm or cancel appointments with one tap, join telehealth sessions from reminders, and securely access lab results and documents via embedded links. Quick-response buttons can also be configured."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Does the system support WhatsApp for patient communication?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. WhatsApp can be used when your clinic integrates its WhatsApp Business account. It is available only for custom notifications and not for automated system alerts."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How are notifications triggered in the system?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Notifications are workflow-driven and sent automatically when specific events occur, such as appointment bookings and reminders, payment confirmations, lab result availability, new consultation documents, and care plan steps."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can staff still send manual notifications when needed?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Authorized staff can send custom notifications in addition to automated workflows. These can be delivered across multiple channels, including WhatsApp if integrated."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Do notifications help reduce patient no-shows?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Automated reminders via SMS, push, and in-app alerts help reduce missed appointments. Actionable notifications with confirmation and rescheduling links improve follow-through."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How are these notifications different from generic tools like email marketing platforms?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Virtual Practice notifications are built into clinical workflows and are healthcare-specific, compliant by default, and tied to patient actions such as rescheduling or viewing documents. No separate tools or data syncing are required."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can notifications reflect my clinic's brand?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Notifications are sent through your clinic's configured email domain, SMS gateway, and optional WhatsApp Business account, ensuring consistent, on-brand communication."}}]}</script><script type="application/ld+json">{"@context":"https://schema.org","@graph":[{"@type":"SoftwareApplication","@id":"#virtual-practice-notifications-app","name":"Virtual Practice — Notifications","applicationCategory":"BusinessApplication","applicationSubCategory":"Healthcare communication & patient engagement","operatingSystem":"Web, iOS, Android","inLanguage":["en"],"provider":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ContinuousCare"},"url":"https://www.continuouscare.io/virtualpractice/","offers":{"@type":"Offer","name":"Free Trial","price":"0","priceCurrency":"USD","availability":"https://schema.org/InStock"},"aggregateRating":{"@type":"AggregateRating","ratingValue":"5","reviewCount":"1"},"featureList":["Automated system notifications for appointments, billing, lab/doc availability, and care plan reminders","Custom notifications for ad-hoc clinic messaging","Multi-channel delivery: email, SMS (via your gateway), mobile push, in-app","Optional WhatsApp (via WhatsApp Business) for Custom Notifications only","Actionable links and buttons (confirm/cancel, join telehealth, view documents)","External messages contain no PHI/PII; sensitive info accessed after login","System notifications can be disabled at the customer level"],"audience":{"@type":"A